In England, in the seven days to 16 February, there were 258,169 new confirmed cases (456.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 February, there were 376,980 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 32% (118,811 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 21 February is 15,888,557 (28,096.4 cases per 100,000 population).
